        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-50" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-48" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;" value="«async return» recoList[v1,v2,v3]" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="426" x="193" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle height="40" width="426" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-51" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-48" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;" value="&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot;&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Async return&lt;/strong&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="261" x="619" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle height="40" width="261" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-52" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-3" style="shape=tableRow;horizontal=0;startSize=0;swimlaneHead=0;swimlaneBody=0;strokeColor=inherit;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;collapsible=0;dropTarget=0;fillColor=none;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="880" y="480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-53" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-52" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;" value="12-14" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="193" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle height="40" width="193" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-54" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-52" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;" value="logEvent(PLAY_START / PROGRESS / END)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="426" x="193" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle height="40" width="426" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-55" parent="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-52" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;" value="&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot;&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Async&lt;/strong&gt; fire-and-forget" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="261" x="619" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle height="40" width="261" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-57" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Step 1 — User clicks Play&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The User triggers clickPlay(videoId) on the WebClient. This starts the whole chain.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps 2–3 — Authentication&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Before anything loads, the WebClient checks with the AuthService to validate the user&#39;s login token (JWT). The AuthService returns either tokenValid or a 401 error. This is where the alt frame kicks in — everything below only happens if the user is authenticated. If not, they get redirected to login.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps 4–5 — Fetch Video Metadata&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Once authenticated, the WebClient asks the VideoService for information about the video — its title, available formats, and DRM key (for copy protection). The VideoService returns this metadata synchronously.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps 6–7 — Request the Video Stream&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The WebClient contacts the StreamServer and requests the video stream, letting the server pick the quality automatically. The StreamServer responds with a stream manifest — an .m3u8 file (HLS format) that acts as a table of contents, telling the player where all the video chunks are.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Step 8 — Video Actually Plays&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The StreamServer starts delivering video chunks continuously using ABR (Adaptive Bitrate) — meaning the quality automatically adjusts up or down depending on the user&#39;s internet speed. This is what actually makes the video play on screen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps 9–10 — Analytics (Fire &amp;amp; Forget)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;While the video plays, the WebClient silently fires off asynchronous events to the Analytics system — first when playback starts (PLAY_START), and again when it ends (PLAY_END with the total duration watched). These are async because they don&#39;t block the video — the player doesn&#39;t wait for a response before continuing.&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="380" width="1140" x="15" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Jpd5OPvAWBVnhis-ZnHx-58" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 30px;&quot;&gt;Here&#39;s a walkthrough of the sequence diagram, step by step:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="1000" x="10" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
